# SQL and Markdown Link Rule

When referencing any SQL or Markdown file in responses:

- Always include a clickable Markdown link to the file path.
- Prefer relative project paths in links (for example, `[Phase 1+2 Test Plan](docs/phase1-phase2-test-plan.md)`).
- If sharing SQL/MD content that already exists in the repo, include the file link before or alongside the content.
- If creating a new SQL/MD file, include a clickable link to that new file in the same response.

Do not provide plain-text-only path mentions for SQL/MD files when a clickable link can be provided.
